text: María Rosa Moreno (born 9 August 1964) is a retired Spanish taekwondo athlete. She competed at the 1988 Summer Olympics, where taekwondo was a demonstration sport, in the finweight event. She won the bronze medal at the 1987 World Taekwondo Championships in the -43 kg category. At the European Taekwondo Championships, she became the European Champion in 1988 She won the silver medal in 1986 and the bronze medal in 1990. == References == Category:1964 births Category:Spanish martial artists
